Krys Shahin and Christopher Buchanan report: State officials are warning at least 1.1 million people across seven states may be impacted by an AssuranceAmerica data breach. Notices about the breach were sent to California, Massachusetts, Nebraska, South Carolina, Texas, Vermont, and Washington residents Friday. AssuranceAmerica Managing General Agency, LLC, said they detected &#8220;suspicious activity&#8221; on...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F06%2F28%2Fassuranceamerica-breach-may-have-affected-more-than-1-1-million-people-in-seven-states%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dassuranceamerica-breach-may-have-affected-more-than-1-1-million-people-in-seven-states&amp;action_name=AssuranceAmerica%20breach%20may%20have%20affected%20more%20than%201.1%20million%20people%20in%20seven%20states&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
